</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[544,638,1438,1464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,638,1438,1498]" box="[151,369,1473,1498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,236,1473,1498]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1541,1563]" captionTargetBox="[319,1266,368,1519]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[302,1284,363,1519]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Busonia micrata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia serrata sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia albilateralis Maldonado-Capriles I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241682/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
Figs. 
<number box="[222,236,1474,1498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A–D, 
<number box="[305,319,1474,1498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" value="4.0">4</number>
F–J)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="547" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1545,2002]" box="[151,800,1545,1570]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1545,1570]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 3.0– 
<quantity box="[714,796,1546,1570]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1545,2002]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
Crown and face brownish with black stripes, ocelli pink (
<figureCitation box="[851,930,1581,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1541,1563]" captionTargetBox="[319,1266,368,1519]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[302,1284,363,1519]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Busonia micrata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia serrata sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia albilateralis Maldonado-Capriles I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241682/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
Figs. 
<number box="[915,930,1582,1606]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D). Pronotum brown, lateral margin more yellowish. Mesoscutum and scutellum dark brown, lateral margin yellowish, basal triangles black brown. Forewing hyaline with light brown tinge, broad band along costa dark brown, 
<number box="[1003,1013,1654,1678]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" value="1.0">1</number>
st apical cell colourless (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1403,1653,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1541,1563]" captionTargetBox="[319,1266,368,1519]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[302,1284,363,1519]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Busonia micrata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia serrata sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia albilateralis Maldonado-Capriles I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241682/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
Fig. 
<number box="[1387,1403,1654,1678]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Mesepimeron dark brown. Legs pale ochraceous, hind leg macrosetae brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1545,2002]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
Male genitalia. Pygofer broadened subapically. Appendage of segment X slender directed posteriorly, in posterior view crossing over each other. Subgenital plate narrow, with several hair-like setae on dorsal and ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[246,316,1797,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[179,1404,182,1653]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1422,169,1665]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Busonia lactata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia micrata sp. nov. F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
Fig. 
<number box="[301,316,1798,1822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Connective with two arms broad, central lobe small. Style tooth on ventral margin, with a few setae on dorsal margin. Aedeagus dorsal margin straight with smaller angular process in lateral view; shaft slightly compressed subapically, lateral margin not smooth, broadened in middle and lower regions slightly concave in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[305,383,1905,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[179,1404,182,1653]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1422,169,1665]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Busonia lactata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia micrata sp. nov. F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
Figs. 
<number box="[369,383,1906,1930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F, G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="547" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1545,2002]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1941,1966]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">Etymology.</emphasis>
